{
  "stem": "3012.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had free time given by the school when we had to observe the religious education.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But mostly at home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It went all right for a while.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, for example, my mother told me that one of her best friend married-- after the First World War-- an officer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when they came back after honeymoon to Salgotarjan and they met mother on the street-- they were very, very close friends-- she turned her head.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So mother understood, and she-- she reacted also in a way that the person became a non-person.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, because she was Jewish, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the officer, of course, the Hungarian officer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But gradually, like on Saturdays-- when I was still going to grammar school-- mother and grandfather used to pick me up, because it happen that the children-- and of course where do the children hear this?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At home-- started mocking Jewish girls.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a co-ed school system in Salgotarjan grammar school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I went to the gymnasium which is something different from what we have here, because a gymnasium here is where you-- exercises and all that, but in Hungary it was the equivalent of junior and senior high school.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] attend four classes at the gymnasium, between age 10 and age 14.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'36 to '40.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Gradually, we felt that there is some pressure in the gymnasium on Jewish girls.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were still not barred from that particular school, but my parents felt that I should follow my studies somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
